context: As the <b6_0>Roman Empire<b6_0/> was falling apart, Palermo fell under the control of several <b4_0>Germanic tribes<b4_0/>. The first were the Vandals in 440 AD under the rule of their king Geiseric. <b5_0>The Vandals<b5_0/> had <a0_0>occupied all the Roman provinces in North Africa by 455<a0_0/> establishing themselves as a significant force. They acquired Corsica, Sardinia and Sicily shortly afterwards. However, they soon lost these newly acquired possessions to the <a1_0>Ostrogoths<a1_0/>. The <b7_0>Ostrogothic<b7_0/> conquest under Theodoric the Great began in 488; <a2_0>Theodoric supported Roman culture and government<a2_0/> unlike the Germanic Goths. <b8_0>The Gothic War<b8_0/> took place between the Ostrogoths and the Eastern Roman Empire, also known as the <a3_0>Byzantine Empire<a3_0/>. Sicily was the first part of Italy to be taken under control of General Belisarius who was commissioned by Eastern Emperor. Justinian I solidified his rule in the following years.
